WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.200 --> 00:00:10.220
Sadhguru: The coming year is a
historic event in many ways.

00:00:10.220 --> 00:00:19.440
United Nations has declared the
World International Yoga Day.

00:00:19.440 --> 00:00:23.380
Over 15,000 years ago, since Adiyogi,

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:28.080
many things have happened 
in terms of propagating yoga,

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:30.940
in terms of  reaching out.

00:00:30.940 --> 00:00:36.100
Many administrations in the
form of kings took to yoga.

00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:41.300
For the first time, the head 
of a major nation on the planet

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:45.700
is talking about yoga in public, 
in international fora.

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:49.620
Speaker: And I invite him to address the Assembly,
Mr. Prime Minister.

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:07.940
Sadhguru: This could be a kind of a foundation stone

00:01:07.980 --> 00:01:14.820
to make scientific approach to the inner
well-being of the human being a worldwide thing,

00:01:14.820 --> 00:01:19.760
that if you want to be well,
you don’t have to seek heaven’s help.

00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:25.040
You can turn inward and fix it.

00:01:25.040 --> 00:01:31.460
This is the message when you say
there is a International Yoga Day&nbsp;-

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:32.940
this is what it means.

00:01:32.940 --> 00:01:39.620
The world is beginning to accept human
well-being is not in heaven, it’s within us.

00:01:39.620 --> 00:01:42.720
It’s a tremendous step for the world

00:01:42.720 --> 00:01:44.400
and for the first time,

00:01:44.400 --> 00:01:49.960
one hundred-and-seventy-seven countries 
get together to pass a resolution.

00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:53.140
Never before in the history of United Nations,

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:59.660
hundred-and-seventy-seven countries 
have voted for anything

00:01:59.660 --> 00:02:03.320
Sadhguru: I want you to understand&nbsp;-
this has lived for over 15,000 years

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:09.380
without any kind of one organization 
pushing it or forcing it.

00:02:09.380 --> 00:02:13.800
Simply because of its efficacy - 
because it works, it’s lived.

00:02:19.780 --> 00:02:26.600
Today, nearly two billion people 
on the planet are doing some form of yoga.

00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:28.020
I am not  happy with that.

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:34.020
I want the 7.2 billion people 
to do some form of yoga because

00:02:34.020 --> 00:02:37.720
in the last hundred years, 
we have ripped the planet apart

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:42.700
but we are nowhere near well-being. 
If human well-being has to happen,

00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:46.680
the only and only way is one has to turn inward.

00:02:46.680 --> 00:02:48.580
There is really no other way

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:52.980
because pain and pleasure 
happens from within you,

00:02:52.980 --> 00:02:55.980
joy and misery 
happens from within you,

00:02:55.980 --> 00:02:59.300
the very light and darkness happens within you.

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:05.120
The only space where you generate
experience is within.

00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:11.280
If you don’t turn inward, fixing your 
well-being on this planet is out of question.

00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:16.900
Today, we have the necessary 
resource, capability, and technology

00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:20.180
to address every human 
problem on the planet.

00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:22.420
Never before was this possible.

00:03:22.420 --> 00:03:28.020
Only thing that’s missing is an inclusive
consciousness of human beings.

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:30.320
And this is what yoga can do -

00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:36.440
beyond religion, beyond belief systems, 
beyond caste, creed race, nationality,

00:03:36.440 --> 00:03:40.040
people can experience a deep sense 
of unity within themselves,

00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:45.140
which is what the world needs. This is a 
momentous step that humanity is taking.

00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:48.200
It is time the world turns inward 
for their well-being.

00:03:48.260 --> 00:03:52.800
Not up, not out, in – 
in is the only way out.

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:57.560
If we want well-being, 
in is the only way out.

